---
title: Image Zoom on Hover
description: Smooth image zoom on hover using CSS transform and `overflow:hidden`.
slug: image-zoom
cssFile: image-zoom.css
explanation: <code>overflow:hidden</code> on the container clips the image when it scales beyond its bounds. The <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> itself gets <code>transform:scale()</code> on <code>:hover</code> with a transition. Because <code>scale()</code> grows from the center, the effect is a smooth zoom-in without shifting the image position. The container dimensions stay fixed throughout.
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center">
	<div class="zoom-wrap">
		<img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/css1/400/260" alt="Hover to zoom">
	</div>
	<div class="zoom-wrap">
		<img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/css2/400/260" alt="Hover to zoom">
	</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<div class="zoom-wrap">
  <img src="image.jpg" alt="Hover to zoom">
</div>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
.zoom-wrap {
  width: 200px;
  height: 130px;
  border-radius: 10px;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.zoom-wrap img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  display: block;
  transition: transform .4s ease;
}

.zoom-wrap:hover img {
  transform: scale(1.15);
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
